def train_list(x):  # 
    train_list = []
    name = ["PM2.5", "PM10", "SO2", "CO", "NO2", "O3_8h"]
    for i in range(x.shape[0]):
        lista = []
        for j in name:
            lista.append(x.iloc[i, :]["{}".format(j)])
        train_list.append(lista)
    return train_list

x = train[["PM2.5", "PM10", "SO2", "CO", "NO2", "O3_8h"]]
y = train[["IPRC"]]
# 
target = y["IPRC"].to_list()
# 
x_train = train_list(x)
# 
liner = LinearRegression()
liner.fit(x_train, target)

# numpy.savez()  npz 
import numpy as np 
 
a = np.array([[1,2,3],[4,5,6]])
b = np.arange(0, 1.0, 0.1)
c = np.sin(b)
# c  sin_array
np.savez("runoob.npz", a, b, sin_array = c)
r = np.load("runoob.npz")  
print(r.files) # 
print(r["arr_0"]) #  a
print(r["arr_1"]) #  b
print(r["sin_array"]) #  c
